# Laravel Backend Conventions

## Invokable Controllers

Use single-action invokable controllers with `__invoke()`. Group them in directories mirroring the URL structure.

```php
// /company/settings -> App\Http\Controllers\Company\Settings\
class SaveRunnerSettingsController extends Controller
{
    public function __invoke(SaveRunnerSettingsRequest $request): RedirectResponse
    {
        // ...
    }
}
```

## Form Requests

Extract validation into FormRequest classes. Never validate inline in controllers. Mirror the controller namespace.

```php
// App\Http\Requests\Company\Settings\SaveRunnerSettingsRequest
class SaveRunnerSettingsRequest extends FormRequest
{
    public function rules(): array
    {
        return ['time' => ['required', 'date_format:H:i']];
    }
}
```

## Route References

Always use `action(Controller::class)` instead of `route('name')` when referring to routes.

```php
// BAD
return redirect()->route('settings.show');
url()->route('settings.show');

// GOOD
return redirect()->action(ShowSettingsController::class);
url()->action(ShowSettingsController::class);
```

## Return Types

Always add explicit return types to public methods, especially `__invoke()`.

## Actions for Domain Logic

Place reusable domain logic in `app/Actions/` with an `execute()` method.

```php
final class NotifyCompany
{
    public function __construct(private Company $company) {}

    public function execute(Notification $notification): void { /* ... */ }
}
```

## Enums for Finite Sets

Use PHP backed enums with helper methods for fixed value sets.

## Custom Casts and DTOs

Use custom Eloquent casts with DTO classes for structured JSON columns. DTOs must implement `JsonSerializable`.
